Seun Kuti, the youngest son of legendary Afrobeat singer, Fela Kuti, has alleged most rich people in Nigeria are into money rituals. The singer argued no African has ever made money without engaging in ritual killings. Taking to his Instagram page, Seun Kuti wrote: “Don’t do money rituals. Don’t kill people for money. Abeg which African rich man no dey kill people for money? “99 per cent of the wealth in the country is earned by sacrificing the lives and destinies of millions of Nigerians, that is the real money ritual!! “Abi na ordinary eye building dey take collapse crush children to death for school? All the lives Wey bad roads dey take? All the avoidable deaths in our hospital? He added: “Listen NIGERIA ITSELF IS A MONEY RITUAL! And all your big men and women are RITUALISTS. “Abi na ordinary eye Hairdresser dey take turn Oil Mogul? Abeg make una shift. #getthesax.” (Thenation)       Seun Kuti, a popular Nigerian singer and son of Late Fela Anikulapo-Kuti has claimed that the Nigerian army and police force were created to kill black people and protect Western interest.   This is coming amidst widespread protest against the activities of SARS officers in the country.   Speaking during… In "Entertainment" Afrobeat singer, Seun Kuti, has attacked the Academic Staff Union of Universities (ASUU) over the group’s silence on sexual harassment in public institutions. Kuti’s reaction followed the publication of the #SexForGrades documentary on Monday by BBC Africa Eye. The 13-minute documentary captured the University of Lagos (UNILAG) and the University… In "Education" Seun Kuti wants you all to stop 'famzing' his late father, Fela Kuti when all you want to do is take advantage of his name. Seun Kuti is shaking a table that has a lot of singers on it following his comments where he said everyone wants to be Fela… In "Entertainment"